cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SOC, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the problem of cross-domain social recommendation, which involves both social networks and information domains. It also leverages user-user connections in social networks and user-item interactions in information domains to make recommendations. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves recommending relevant items to users. 

Additionally, it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel Neural Social Collaborative Ranking approach that uses embeddings to learn user and item representations. 

It may also be categorized under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it deals with social networks and user-user connections. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves natural language processing and text-based features.
